{"title_page": "Bigg Boss", "text_new": "\n\n|tv             = ''Bigg Boss'' (independent versions for languages, [[Bigg Boss#Summary|see below]])\n|otherlabel1    = Languages\n|otherdata1     = 7<br>''([[Bengali language|Bengali]], [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Kannada language|Kannada]], [[Malayalam]], [[Marathi language|Marathi]], [[Hindi language|Hindi]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]])''\n|otherlabel2    = Produced by\n|otherdata2     = [[Endemol|EndemolShine India]]\n|otherlabel3    = Based on\n|otherdata3     = [[Big Brother (franchise)|''Big Brother'']]\n|website        = {{URL|https://endemolshineindia.in/key-shows/biggboss/}}\n}}\n'''''Bigg Boss''''' is an Indian [[Reality television#Reality competition/game shows|reality television game show]]  franchise produced by [[Endemol#Endemol India|EndemolShine India]] through [[Viacom 18]] and [[Viacom 18|Colors]], broadcast in [[India]], subsequently it is [[Broadcast syndication|syndicated]] internationally and made available online as [[Video on demand|VOD]] through [[Over-the-top media services|OTT]] platforms in [[Hotstar]] and [[Voot]]. There have been 7 versions of the show in 7 individual languages spoken in the Indian subcontinent. The first show of the franchise was ''[[Bigg Boss (Hindi TV series)|Bigg Boss]]'' in [[Hindi]] which debuted in 2006. The franchise has extended its presence in [[Kannada]], [[Bengali language|Bengali]] in 2013 and [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]] in 2017 and [[Marathi language|Marathi]] and [[Malayalam]] as of 2018. Though only celebrities were selected to be the housemates in the initial seasons, general public have been auditioned to be on the show in the latest seasons of [[Bigg Boss (Hindi TV series)|Hindi]], [[Bigg Boss Kannada|Kannada]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2017/apply-online-for-bigg-boss-kannada-season-5-264880.html|title=Grab Your Only Chance To Be A Participant On The Reality Show Bigg Boss Kananda Season 5|last=|first=|date=2017-07-07|work=www.filmibeat.com|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en}}</ref> and [[Bigg Boss Telugu|Telugu]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/bigg-boss-telugu-season-2-auditions-5163661/|title=Bigg Boss Telugu Season 2: Auditions open for commoners|date=2018-05-04|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en-US}}</ref> versions of the show.\n\n== Synopsis ==\nIn this show, contestants called \"housemates\" live together in a specially constructed house that is isolated from the outside world. Housemates are voted out (usually on a weekly basis) until only one remains and wins the cash prize. During their stay in the house, contestant are continuously monitored by live television cameras as well as personal audio microphones.\n\n== Premise ==\nThe program relies on techniques such as a stripped back-to-basic environment, evictions, weekly tasks and competitions set by ''Bigg Boss'', and the \"Confession Room\" where housemates convey their private thoughts to the camera and reveal their number of their fellow housemates whom they wish to be evicted from the house. The housemates with the most nominations are then announced, and viewers are given the opportunity to vote (via [[SMS]] or online through social media and smartphone applications) for the nominee they wish to be evicted or to be saved from eviction. The remaining last person is declared the winner.\n\nThe contestants are required to indulge in housework and are assigned tasks by the producers of the show (who communicate with the housemates via the omnipresent authority figure known to them only as \"Bigg Boss\"). The tasks are designed to test the teamwork abilities and community spirit of the housemates. The housemates' \"luxury budget\" (weekly allowance to buy luxury food items other than the supplied essentials) depends on the outcome of assigned tasks.\n\n== History ==\n\n=== Creation ===\n''Bigg Boss'' is a [[Hindi]] ([[Bollywood]]) adaption of [[Big Brother (franchise)|''Big Brother'']] created in [[Big Brother (Dutch TV series)|Netherlands]] by [[John de Mol Jr.]], largely based on the ''[[Celebrity Big Brother]]'' model owned by the [[Endemol Shine Group]]. The show was named ''Bigg Boss'' and a house was constructed for the purpose of the show at [[Lonavla]] in [[Maharashtra]] (Season 1 to 4 and 6 to 12), in Karjat (Season 5), in [[Goregaon]] (Season 13) . ''Bigg Boss'' debuted on television in 2006 through [[Sony Entertainment Television]] with [[Arshad Warsi]] as the host. The show gained popularity after [[Shilpa Shetty]] emerged as the winner<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/6308443.stm|title=Shetty wins Celebrity Big Brother|date=2007|access-date=2018-06-21|language=en-GB}}</ref> in [[Celebrity Big Brother 5 (UK)]] and replaced Warsi as the host in the [[Bigg Boss 2|second season]] of ''Bigg Boss''. From the second season, the show has moved to [[Viacom 18]]'s [[Colors TV|Colors.]]\n\n=== Expansion ===\nThe show's acceptance and success among the Indian audience paved way for its expansion into other [[Languages of India|Indian languages]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/indian-big-brother-expands-regional-425064http:|title=Indian \u2018Big Brother\u2019 Expands With Regional Language Versions|last=|first=|date=|work=Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2008-06-22}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> After the [[Bigg Boss 6|sixth season]] was completed in Hindi in 2013, ''[[Bigg Boss Kannada|Kannada]]''<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-bigg-boss-gets-kannada-makeover-1805693|title='Bigg Boss' gets Kannada makeover|date=2013-02-28|work=dna|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en-US}}</ref> and ''[[Bigg Boss Bangla|Bengali]]'' adaptions were created by [[Endemol]] through [[ETV Network]] with the same house and resources with [[Sudeep]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/regional/sudeep-to-play-salman-khan-in-kannada-version-of-bigg-boss_128946.html|title=Sudeep to play Salman Khan in Kannada version of `Bigg Boss`|date=2013-02-28|work=Zee News|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en}}</ref> and [[Mithun Chakraborty]] as hosts respectively. While the Kannada version became an instant hit,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/release/y2k13/apr/aprrel8.php|title=ETV Kannada\u2019s - Bigg Boss a BIGG hit with the Audience|date=2013-04-05|work=Indian Television Dot Com|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en}}</ref> Bengali version did not turn out to be very successful. The Kannada version saw its subsequent seasons annually, similar to Hindi while Bengali version has completed only 2 seasons in 6 years.\n\nUpon completion of 10 seasons in Hindi, 4 seasons in Kannada and 2 seasons in Bengali, Endemol extended its presence in [[South India]] by creating [[Bigg Boss Tamil|Tamil]] and [[Bigg Boss (Telugu TV series)|Telugu]] versions of the show with Star India in 2017 and roped in [[Kamal Haasan]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/58491108.cms|title=Official: Kamal Haasan to host 'BIGG BOSS' Tamil - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> and [[Jr NTR]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/after-kamal-haasan-jr-ntr-to-host-bigg-boss-in-telugu/story-iYbzYijJiFyKNMPlAwOAVL.html|title=After Kamal Haasan, Jr NTR to host Bigg Boss in Telugu|last=|first=|date=2017-05-30|work=www.hindustantimes.com|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en}}</ref> as hosts respectively. In 2018, the show has been adapted to [[Bigg Boss Marathi|Marathi]] with Viacom 18 and hosted by [[Mahesh Manjrekar]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/viacom18-to-launch-bigg-boss-marathi/articleshow/63384279.cms|title=Viacom18 to launch Bigg Boss Marathi|last=Laghate|first=Gaurav|date=2018-03-20|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> and in [[Malayalam]] as ''[[Bigg Boss (Malayalam TV series)|Bigg Boss]]'' with [[Star India]] and [[Mohanlal]] as the host.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.exchange4media.com/media-tv/bigg-boss-all-set-to-enter-marathi-homes-_89325.html|title=Bigg Boss all set to enter Marathi homes|work=Indian Advertising Media & Marketing News \u2013 exchange4media|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.televisionpost.com/asianet-ropes-in-mohanlal-as-host-for-bigg-boss-malayalam/|title=Asianet ropes in Mohanlal as host for Bigg Boss Malayalam|website=www.televisionpost.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref>\n\n== Summary ==\n\n:{{color box|#90EE90}} Currently airing (1)\n:{{color box|#fff2a5}} Recently concluded (5)\n:{{color box|#FFA500}} No longer airing (1)\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 80%;text-align:center;\"\n!Language\n!Show\n!Season\n!Year\n!'''Official Name'''\n!Primary<br>Network\n!Online<br>VOD\n!House<br>Location\n!Premiere\n!Finale\n!Days\n!Housemates\n!Prize Money\n!Host\n!Voice of<br>Bigg Boss\n!Winner\n!Runner Up\n|-\n|rowspan=\"14\" style=\"background: #fff2a5;\" |[[Hindi]]\n| rowspan=\"14\" |''[[Bigg Boss (Hindi TV series)|Bigg Boss Hindi]]''\n|[[Bigg Boss (Hindi season 1)|1]]\n|2006\u201307\n|Bigg Boss\n|[[Sony Entertainment Television (India)|Sony]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |N/A\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Lonavla|Lonavala]]\n|3 November 2006\n|26 January 2007\n|86\n| rowspan=\"3\" |15\n| rowspan=\"5\" |{{INRConvert|1|c}}\n|[[Arshad Warsi]]\n| rowspan=\"14\" |[[Atul Kapoor]]\n|style=\"background:cyan;\" |[[Rahul Roy]]\n|style=\"background:pink;\" |[[Carol Gracias]]\n|-\n|[[Bigg Boss (Hindi season 2)|2]]\n|2008\n|Bigg Boss Season 2\n| rowspan=\"13\" |[[Viacom 18|Colors]]\n|17 August 2008\n|22 November 2008\n|98\n|[[Shilpa Shetty]]\n|style=\"background:cyan;\" |[[Ashutosh Kaushik]]\n|style=\"background:cyan;\" |[[Raja Chaudhary]]\n|-\n|[[Bigg Boss (Hindi season 3)|3]]\