=\"3\" |''[[Bigg Boss (Telugu TV series)|Bigg Boss<br>Telugu]]''\n|[[Bigg Boss Telugu 1|1]]\n|2017\n|Bigg Boss\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Star Maa|Star<br>Maa]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Hotstar]]\n|[[Lonavla|Lonavala]]\n|16 July 2017\n|24 September 2017\n|70\n|16\n| rowspan=\"3\" |{{INRConvert|50|l}}\n|[[Jr NTR]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Radha Krishna\n|style=\"background:cyan;\" |[[Siva Balaji]]\n| style=\"background:cyan;\" |[[Aadarsh Balakrishna]]\n|-\n|[[Bigg Boss Telugu 2|2]]\n|2018\n|Bigg Boss 2\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Hyderabad]]\n|10 June 2018\n|30 September 2018\n|112\n|18\n|[[Nani (actor)|Nani]]\n|style=\"background:cyan;\"|[[Kaushal Manda]]\n|style=\"background:pink;\"|[[Geetha Madhuri]]\n|-\n|[[Bigg Boss Telugu 3|3]]\n|2019\n|Bigg Boss 3\n|21 July 2019\n|3 November 2019\n|105\n|17\n|[[Akkineni Nagarjuna]]\n----[[Ramya Krishnan]]\n|style=\"background:cyan;\"|[[Rahul Sipligunj]]\n|style=\"background:pink;\"|[[Sreemukhi]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"17\" |\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#fff2a5;\" |[[Marathi language|Marathi]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Bigg Boss Marathi|Bigg Boss<br>Marathi]]''\n|[[Bigg Boss Marathi 1|1]]\n|2018\n|Bigg Boss \u092e\u0930\u093e\u0920\u0940\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Colors Marathi|Colors<br>Marathi]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Voot]]\n|[[Lonavla|Lonavala]]\n|15 April 2018\n|22 July 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\" |98\n|18\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{INRConvert|50|l}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Mahesh Manjrekar]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Ratnakar Tardalkar\n|style=\"background:pink;\" |[[Megha Dhade]]\n| style=\"background:cyan;\" |[[Pushkar Jog]]\n|-\n|[[Bigg Boss Marathi 2|2]]\n|2019\n|Bigg Boss \u092e\u0930\u093e\u0920\u0940 2\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Mumbai]]\n|26 May 2019\n|1 September 2019\n|17\n|style=\"background:cyan;\"|Shiv Thakre\n|style=\"background:pink;\"|Neha Shitole\n|-\n| colspan=\"17\" |\n|-\n|rowspan=2 style=\"background:#90EE90;\" | [[Malayalam]]\n|rowspan=2| ''[[Bigg Boss (Malayalam TV series)|Bigg Boss<br>Malayalam]]''\n|[[Bigg Boss (Malayalam season 1)|1]]\n|2018\n|Bigg Boss\n|rowspan=2|[[Asianet (TV channel)|Asianet]]\n|rowspan=2|[[Hotstar]]\n|[[Lonavla|Lonavala]]\n|24 June 2018\n|30 September 2018\n|98\n|18\n| {{INRConvert|1|c}}\n|rowspan=2| [[Mohanlal]]\n|rowspan=2| N/A\n| style=\"background:cyan;\" |[[Sabumon Abdusamad]]\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |[[Pearle Maaney]]\n|-\n|[[Bigg Boss (Malayalam season 2)|2]]\n| 2020\n|Bigg Boss\n| [[Chennai]]\n| 5 January 2020\n| 20 March 2020\n| 74\n| 23\n| {{INRConvert|50|l}}\n| Cancelled\n| Cancelled\n|}\n\n{{Color box|cyan|border=darkgray}} Male Winners.  {{Color box|pink|border=darkgray}} Female Winners.\n\n== Versions ==\n\n=== Bigg Boss Hindi ===\n{{Main|Bigg Boss (Hindi TV series)}}\n''Bigg Boss'' is the Hindi version of the show<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://endemolshineindia.in/key-shows/biggboss/|title=Bigg boss \u2013 Endemol|website=endemolshineindia.in|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> and the first version of the franchise. The first season premiered in 2006 on [[Sony Entertainment Television]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/sony-endemol-lock-horns-over-big-boss-108012101043_1.html|title=Sony, Endemol lock horns over Big Boss|last=Sheikh|first=Aminah|date=2008-01-21|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref> with [[Arshad Warsi]] as the host<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevisionacademy.com/site/awards_hhita_details_new.php?year=2007|title=The Indian Television Academy Awards|date=2014-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006030252/http://www.indiantelevisionacademy.com/site/awards_hhita_details_new.php?year=2007|archive-date=2014-10-06|url-status=dead|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> with.  {{INRConvert|1|c}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/juhi-parmar-wins-bigg-boss-season-5-88824-2012-01-07|title=Juhi Parmar wins Bigg Boss 5, takes home Rs.1 crore|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> as the prize money. The license for ''Bigg Boss'' was acquired by Viacom 18 and the next season was aired on [[Viacom 18|Colors]] with [[Shilpa Shetty]] as the show's host.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/tv/shilpa-shetty-ousts-arshad-warsi/story-mqnV6jQRocdFj83mgY6iyL.html|title=Shilpa Shetty ousts Arshad Warsi|last=|first=|date=2008-07-23|work=www.hindustantimes.com|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en}}</ref> Veteran actor [[Amitabh Bachchan|Amithabh Bachchan]] was roped in to play host<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fulldhamaal.com/current-affairs/amitabh-bachchans-big-boss-3-stand-at-first-in-trp-raceinteresting-33181.htm|title=Amitabh Bachchan\u2019s Big Boss 3 stand at first in TRP Race!\u2026(Interesting)|work=Latest News, Opinion, Product Review & Entertainment-FullDhamaal.com|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref> for the third season while [[Salman Khan]] appeared as the host in the fourth season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-tv-bigg-boss-4-review/20101004.htm|title=Wild days ahead on Bigg Boss 4!|work=Rediff|access-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> The fifth season was jointly hosted<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/salman-khan-sanjay-dutt-to-host-bigg-boss-five/20110720.htm|title=Salman-Sanjay Dutt to host Bigg Boss together - Rediff.com Movies |website=www.rediff.com|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref> by Sanjay Dutt and Salman Khan while Salman alone continues to host the show consecutively since sixth season<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.talkbollywood.com/salman-khan-to-host-bigg-boss-6/|title=Salman Khan to host Bigg Boss 6|last=Bollywood|first=Talk|work=Talk Bollywood|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref> till date.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/bigg-boss-9-update-salman-khan-to-host-promos-to-be-out-soon/|title=\u2018Bigg Boss 9\u2019 update: Salman Khan to host, promos to be out soon|date=2015-09-03|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.india.com/showbiz/salman-khan-asks-are-you-ready-for-bigg-boss-10-and-shares-bigg-boss-10-promo-inviting-contestants-1082117/|title=Salman Khan asks \u2018Are you ready for Bigg Boss 10?\u2019 and shares Bigg Boss 10 promo inviting contestants!|last=Parande|first=Shweta|date=2016-04-04|work=India.com|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/entertainment/bigg-boss-11-salman-khan-earns-rs-11-crore-per-episode-fee-his-reaction-and-cheap-shot-by-colleague-will-floor-you/873132/|title=Bigg Boss 11: Salman Khan earns Rs 11 crore per episode fee? His reaction and cheap shot by colleague will floor you|date=2017-09-27|work=The Financial Express|access-date=2018-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref> A lavish purpose-built house (with annual modifications) at [[Lonavla|Lonavala]], [[Mumbai]] was used for the show<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2009/oct/08/slide-show-1-sneak-peek-into-bigg-boss-house.htm|title=What really goes on in Bigg Boss house?|work=Rediff|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> in the first five seasons while a new house was built house at [[ND Studios|Big ND Studios]] in [[Karjat]], [[Pune]] for the fifth season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-what-the-bigg-boss-house-is-going-to-be-like/20110930.htm|title=What the Bigg Boss house is going to be like this season|work=Rediff|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> The house at Lonavala was rebuilt and used from the sixth season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.planetbollywood.com/displayArticle.php?id=n061312022039|title=Bigg Boss Back To Lonavala! - Planet Bollywood News|website=www.planetbollywood.com|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> The prize has been reduced to {{INRConvert|50|l}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/bigg-boss-11-winner-shilpa-shinde-bags-the-trophy-walks-away-with-the-prize-money-of-rs-44-lakhs/articleshow/62497901.cms|title=Bigg Boss 11 winner: Shilpa Shinde bags the trophy - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> from the fifth season. A spin off show \u2014 ''[[Bigg Boss Halla Bol|Bigg Boss: Halla Bol]]'' \u2014 was launched and merged into the eighth season with 5 finalists ('Champions') from eighth season and 5 previous runners-up ('Challengers') which was hosted by Farah Khan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.india.com/buzz/bigg-boss-halla-bol-farah-khan-to-host-bigg-boss-8-with-challengers-watch-promo-233744/|title=Bigg Boss Halla Bol: Farah Khan to host Bigg Boss 8 with challengers! Watch promo|last=Service|first=Indo-Asian News|date=2014-12-28|work=India.com|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThough the show has largely been a celebrity-only show, it opened the doors for participation by the common people from the tenth season.\n\n[[Atul Kapoor]] has been the 'voice' of ''Bigg Boss'' since the first season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/tv-happy-birthday-bigg-boss-atul-kapoor-bigg-boss-voice-bb-11-419263|title=Happy birthday Bigg Boss: Meet the mysterious man behind Bigg Boss voice|date=2017-12-28|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nThe winners of each season are Rahul Roy,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.youtube.com/AmeeriVlogs|title= Rahul Roy wins Bigg Boss TV reality show|last=|first=|date=2007-01-27|work=Youtube|access-date=2018-06-21|url-status=live|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Ashutosh Kaushik]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/winners-of-bigg-boss/bigg-boss-2-winner-ashutosh-kaushik/photostory/50697328.cms|title=Bigg Boss 2 winner: Ashutosh Kaushik - Winners of Bigg Boss  {{!}} The Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Vindu Dara Singh]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/vindu-dara-singh-wins-bigg-boss-season-three/559720/|title=Vindu Dara Singh wins 'Bigg Boss' season three - Indian Express|website=archive.indianexpress.com|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Shweta Tiwari]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/winners-of-bigg-boss/Bigg-Boss-4-winner-Shweta-Tiwari/photostory/50697316.cms|title=Bigg Boss 4 winner: Shweta Tiwari - Winners of Bigg Boss  {{!}} The Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Juhi Parmar]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/winners-of-bigg-boss/Bigg-Boss-5-winner-Juhi-Parmar/photostory/50697309.cms|title=Bigg Boss 5 winner: Juhi Parmar - Winners of Bigg Boss  {{!}} The Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Urvashi Dholakia]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/winners-of-bigg-boss/bigg-boss-6-winner-urvashi-dholakia/photostory/50697300.cms|title=Bigg Boss 6 winner: Urvashi Dholakia - Winners of Bigg Boss  {{!}} The Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Gauhar Khan]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tv/bollywood-actress-gauahar-khan-wins-bigg-boss-7_-119730.html|title=Bollywood Actress Gauhar Khan Wins Bigg Boss 7|work=indiatimes.com|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en}}</ref> [[Gautam Gulati]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-bigg-boss-halla-bol-gautam-gulati-crowned-the-winner-2057107|title=Bigg Boss Halla Bol: Gautam Gulati crowned the winner|date=2015-01-31|work=dna|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Prince Narula]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/prince-narula-wins-bigg-boss-9-takes-home-rs-35-lakh/articleshow/50703232.cms|title=Prince Narula wins 'Bigg Boss 9', takes home Rs 35 lakh|date=2016|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Manveer Gurjar]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/manveer-gurjar-wins-bigg-boss-10-why-he-was-the-most-deserving-contestant-3226688.html/amp|title=Manveer Gurjar wins Bigg Boss 10: Why he was the most deserving contestant - Entertainment News, Firstpost|work=Firstpost|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en-US}}</ref>[[Shilpa Shinde]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/bigg-boss-11-finale-live-updates-race-for-the-trophy-begins/articleshow/62498308.cms|title=Bigg Boss 11 Finale episode Highlights: Shilpa Shinde is the winner of the show - Times of India \u25ba|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Dipika Kakar]] and [[Sidharth Shukla]]\n\n=== Bigg Boss Kannada ===\n{{Main|Bigg Boss Kannada}}\n''Bigg Boss Kannada'' is the Kannada version of the show<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://endemolshineindia.in/key-shows/biggboss-kanada/|title=Biggboss \u2013Kanada \u2013 Endemol|website=endemolshineindia.in|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> was the first south Indian adaption<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.endemolindia.com/endemol-lands-regional-market-deals-for-indian-big-brother/|title=Endemol Lands Regional Market Deals for Indian Big Brother|website=www.endemolindia.com|accessdate=6 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924000454/http://www.endemolindia.com/endemol-lands-regional-market-deals-for-indian-big-brother/|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-bigg-boss-gets-kannada-makeover-1805693|title='Bigg Boss' gets Kannada makeover|date=2013-02-28|work=dna|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-US}}</ref> of ''Bigg Boss''. Actor [[Sudeep]] was roped in by [[ETV Kannada]]<ref name=\"auto\"/> to play the host<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/regional/sudeep-to-play-salman-khan-in-kannada-version-of-bigg-boss_128946.html|title=Sudeep to play Salman Khan in Kannada version of `Bigg Boss`|date=2013-02-28|work=Zee News|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en}}</ref> of the show for the first season in 2013. Star India acquired the license for the show and the second season was aired on [[Asianet Suvarna|Suvarna]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/regional/suvarna-sets-high-hopes-with-bigg-boss-kannada-2-140624|title=Suvarna sets high hopes with Bigg Boss Kannada 2|date=2014-06-24|work=Indian Television Dot Com|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en}}</ref> with Sudeep continuing his role as the host of the show. The same house at Lonavala, Pune which was used for the Hindi version was used for the first two seasons of ''Bigg Boss Kannada''. A new and bigger house was constructed at Innovative Film City in [[Bidadi]], [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]] and is being used since the third season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/151028/entertainment-tvmusic/article/bigg-boss|title=Bigg Boss location has been exclusively shifted from Pune to Namma Bengaluru|last=|first=|date=2015-10-28|work=www.deccanchronicle.com|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kannadaprabha.com/cinema/news/bigg-boss-kannada-shooting-set-shifted-to-bidadi/255207.html|title=\u0cac\u0cbf\u0c97\u0ccd\u200c\u0cac\u0cbe\u0cb8\u0ccd\u200c \u0cae\u0cc2\u0cb0\u0ca8\u0cc7 \u0c86\u0cb5\u0cc3\u0ca4\u0ccd\u0ca4\u0cbf \u0cb6\u0cc2\u0c9f\u0cbf\u0c82\u0c97\u0ccd\u200c \u0caa\u0cc1\u0ca3\u0cc6 \u0cac\u0ca6\u0cb2\u0cc1 \u0cac\u0cbf\u0ca1\u0ca6\u0cbf\u0caf\u0cb2\u0ccd\u0cb2\u0cbf|last=|first=|date=|work=www.kannadaprabha.com|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> Sudeep's contract to host the show was extended<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2015/omg-what-is-sudeep-remuneration-for-hosting-bigg-boss-191215.html|title=OMG! What Is Sudeep's Remuneration To Host Bigg Boss?|last=|first=|date=2015-07-20|work=www.filmibeat.com|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en}}</ref> to 5 seasons starting with the third season which returned<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/bigg-boss-kannada-back-on-colors-kannada-115101700639_1.html|title=Bigg Boss Kannada back on Colors Kannada|last=Reporter|first=B. S.|date=2015-10-17|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> to Viacom 18's Colors Kannada. The fifth season moved<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bestmediainfo.com/2017/10/bigg-boss-kannada-season-5-moves-to-colors-super/|title=Bigg Boss Kannada season 5 moves to Colors Super|website=www.bestmediaifo.com|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> to Colors Super, a sister channel of Colors Kannada. It is notable that the Kannada version is the only adaption where the host, Sudeep alone would be hosting the show for seven consecutive seasons. All the seasons so far have had {{INRConvert|50|l}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/kannada/Heres-what-Akul-Balaji-won-from-Bigg-Boss/articleshow/45010572.cms|title=Here's what Akul Balaji won from Bigg Boss 2 - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> as the prize money. Commoners were allowed to be a part of the show from the fifth season through auditions.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2017/apply-online-for-bigg-boss-kannada-season-5-264880.html|title=Grab Your Only Chance To Be A Participant On The Reality Show, Bigg Boss Kananda Season 5|last=|first=|date=2017-07-07|work=www.filmibeat.com|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en}}</ref> Three artists have been the 'voice' of ''Bigg Boss'' as of fifth season - [[Amit Bhargav]] for the first two, B M Venkatesh for the third and Srinivas Prasad since the fourth season.\n\n[[Vijay Raghavendra]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/2013/jul/01/An-unexpected-win-492408.html|title=Vijay Raghavendra's unexpected win|last=|first=|date=|work=The New Indian Express|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Akul Balaji]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2014/bigg-boss-kannada-season-2-winner-akul-balaji-160875.html|title=Bigg Boss Kannada Season 2 Winner: Akul Balaji|last=|first=|date=2014-10-05|work=www.filmibeat.com|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en}}</ref> [[Shruti (actress)|Shruti]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/south-masala/shruthi-wins-kannada-bigg-boss-season-3/articleshow/50794324.cms|title=Shruthi wins Kannada Bigg Boss Season 3|website=Bangalore Mirror|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> Pratham,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/kannada/pratham-wins-bigg-boss/articleshow/56865974.cms|title=Pratham wins Bigg Boss - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Chandan Shetty]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/kannada/bigg-boss-kannada-season-5-winner-chandan-shetty-bags-the-coveted-title/articleshow/62686447.cms|title=Bigg Boss Kannada Season 5: Chandan Shetty is the winner - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> and [[Shashi Kumar (agriculturist)|Shashi Kumar]] have been the winners of the first six seasons of the show respectively. [[Shine Shetty]] is the winner of [[Bigg Boss Kannada (season 7)|season 7]].\n\n=== Bigg Boss Bangla ===\n{{Main|Bigg Boss Bangla}}\n''Bigg Boss Bangla'' is the Bengali version of the show<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://endemolshineindia.in/key-shows/bigg-boss-bangla/|title=Bigg Boss- Bangla \u2013 Endemol|website=endemolshineindia.in|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> which was produced by ETV Bangla with [[Mithun Chakraborty]] as the host<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.afaqs.com/news/story/37795_Bigg-Boss-sets-out-to-capture-Bengali-nights|title=Bigg Boss sets out to capture Bengali nights|website=www.afaqs.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref> while the first season of the Kannada version was wrapping up in 2013. The second season was aired on Colors Bangla in 2016 and was hosted by Bengali actor [[Jeet (actor)|Jeet]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/Jeet-to-host-Bigg-Boss-Bangla-season-2/articleshow/51089112.cms|title=Jeet to host Bigg Boss Bangla season 2? - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref> The Lonavala house used for Hindi version was used<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1130617/jsp/t2/story_17016040.jsp#.UcsFPTt6ySo|title=Living it up in the bigg boss bangla house for 24 hours!|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> in both seasons and the prize money for the show has been lesser than the other adaptions with {{INRConvert|20|l}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1130918/jsp/t2/story_17360142.jsp|title=Aneek Dhar on life after Bigg Boss Bangla|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> and {{INRConvert|35|l}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1160712/jsp/t2/story_96055.jsp|title=Joyjit Banerjee aces Bigg Boss Bangla Season 2|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> respectively for the first and second seasons. This is the only adaption of the show that does not follow the annual format and the seasons have been produced once in 3 years.\n\nAneek Dhar<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/anik-dhar-wins-bengali-bigg-boss-season-1|title=Anik Dhar wins Bengali Bigg Boss season 1|last=Team|first=Tellychakkar|work=Tellychakkar.com|access-date=2018-06-21|language=en}}</ref> and Joyjit Banerjee<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/Joyjit-wins-Bigg-Boss-Bangla-Priya-fans-cry-foul/articleshow/53152062.cms|title=Joyjit wins Bigg Boss Bangla, Priya fans cry foul - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> have been the winners of the first and second season of the show respectively.\n\n=== Bigg Boss Tamil ===\n{{Main|Bigg Boss Tamil}}\n''Bigg Boss Tamil'' is the Tamil version<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://endemolshineindia.in/key-shows/biggboss-kanada-2-2/|title=Biggboss \u2013Tamil \u2013 Endemol|website=endemolshineindia.in|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> of the show and the second south Indian adaption of ''Bigg Boss''. Star India produced the show in 2017 with Kamal Hassan as the host<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/kamal-haasan-all-setto-host-tamil-big-boss/article18203914.ece|title=Kamal Haasan all set to host Tamil Big Boss|last=Reporter|first=Staff|date=2017-04-25|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> on Star Vijay.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://cinema.vikatan.com/tamil-cinema/news/86984-big-boss-reality-show-in-vijay-tv-anchor-by-kamal.html|title=\u0b95\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bca\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd, \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9c\u0baf\u0bcd \u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u2018\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb8\u0bcd\u2019 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb4\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe? #BigBoss {{!}} Big Boss reality show in Vijay TV anchor by kamal|last=M.K.SenthilKumar|first=|date=2017-04-19|work=www.vikatan.com|access-date=2018-06-26|language=ta}}</ref> This has been the only version to have none of its seasons shot at Lonavala. The house for ''Bigg Boss Tamil'' was constructed at EVP Film City, [[Chennai]] and is being used since the first season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/bigg-boss-tamil-season-2-house-5220454/|title=Inside the Bigg Boss Tamil Season 2 house|date=2018-06-17|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en-US}}</ref> All the three seasons so far have had {{INRConvert|50|l}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/bigg-boss-tamil-ends-aarav-wins-grand-prize-rs-50-lakh-69255|title='Bigg Boss' Tamil ends: Aarav wins the grand prize of Rs 2 cores |date=2017-10-01|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> as the prize money. The winners of the show's seasons were [[Aarav]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/tv/bigg-boss-tamil-winner-aarav-s-victory-has-stunned-the-audience/story-JfoYa7wvMYjPWlovqASAgL.html|title=Bigg Boss Tamil grand finale: Aarav\u2019s victory has stunned Twitter|last=|first=|date=2017-10-01|work=www.hindustantimes.com|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en}}</ref> [[Riythvika]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/live-bigg-boss-tamil-2-winner-grand-finale-vijayalakshmi-aishwarya-riythvika-runner-up-781923 | title=Bigg Boss Tamil 2 grand finale: Riythvika is the WINNER | publisher=IB Times | accessdate=30 September 2018}}</ref> and Mugen Rao.<ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/mugen-rao-wins-bigg-boss-tamil-3-sandy-runner-110076</ref>\n\n=== Bigg Boss (Telugu) ===\n{{Main|Bigg Boss (Telugu TV series)}}\n''Bigg Boss Telugu'' is the Telugu version<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://endemolshineindia.in/key-shows/biggboss-kanada-2/|title=Biggboss \u2013Telugu \u2013 Endemol|website=endemolshineindia.in|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> of the show and was produced by Star India on Star Maa with [[Jr NTR]] as the host<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/junior-ntrs-bigg-boss-is-the-most-expensive-telugu-show-details-here-1720627|title=Junior NTR's Bigg Boss Is The 'Most Expensive' Telugu Show. Details Here|work=NDTV.com|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref> and the Lonavala house was used for the first season. The second season is being hosted by [[Nani (actor)|Nani]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/nani-replace-jr-ntr-bigg-boss-season-2-81803|title=Nani to replace Jr NTR in 'Bigg Boss' Season 2|date=2018-05-23|work=The News Minute|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> and a newly built house at [[Annapurna Studios]], [[Hyderabad]] is being used for the show.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Tollywood/2018-06-11/Big-Boss-Season-2-begins-with-a-bang/388105|title=Big Boss Season 2 begins with a bang|website=The Hans India|language=en|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> The third season is being hosted by [[Akkineni Nagarjuna]]. [[Ramya Krishnan]] was the guest host in week 6 of Bigg Boss Telugu Season 3. For this Season house was continued at [[Annapurna Studios]],Hyderabad. The Three Seasons so far have had {{INRConvert|50|l}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/reality-tv/story/congratulations-siva-balaji-wins-bigg-boss-telugu-takes-home-prize-money-of-rs-50-lakh-lifetv-1051788-2017-09-25|title=Congratulations! Siva Balaji wins Bigg Boss Telugu, takes home prize money of Rs 50 lakh|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2018-06-21}}</ref> as the prize money.\n\n[[Siva Balaji]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/bigg-boss-telugu-winner-siva-balaji-is-declared-the-winner-and-adarsh-the-runner-up/articleshow/60820623.cms|title=Bigg Boss Telugu Winner: Siva Balaji is declared the winner and Adarsh the runner-up - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> [[Kaushal Manda]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bigg-boss-telugu-2-grand-finale-live-updates-who-among-5-contestants-will-be-winner-781903 | title=Bigg Boss Telugu 2: Kaushal is winner and he donates prize money to treat women cancer patients | publisher=IB Times | accessdate=30 September 2018}}</ref> and [[Rahul Sipligunj]] are the winners of the first,second and third seasons of the show.\n\n=== Bigg Boss Marathi ===\n{{Main|Bigg Boss Marathi}}\n''Bigg Boss Marathi'' is the Marathi version of the show and the first season is being aired on Viacom 18's Colors Marathi.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.exchange4media.com/media-tv/marathi-television-gets-its-bigg-boss-on-colors-marathi_88999.html|title=Marathi Television gets its Bigg Boss on Colors Marathi|work=Indian Advertising Media & Marketing News \u2013 exchange4media|access-date=2018-06-20|language=en-US}}</ref> The Lonavala house is being used<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/marathi/bigg-boss-marathi-to-be-shot-in-the-house-used-for-hindi-version/articleshow/63580670.cms|title=Bigg Boss Marathi to be shot in the house used for Hindi version - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> for this version and [[Mahesh Manjrekar]] is playing the host.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-in/entertainment/bollywood/mahesh-manjrekar-to-host-bigg-boss-marathi/ar-BBKmwks|title=Mahesh Manjrekar to host Bigg Boss Marathi|website=www.msn.com|language=en-IN|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/marathi/bigg-boss-marathi-here-is-what-host-mahesh-manjrekar-has-to-say-about-marathi-manus/articleshow/63683382.cms|title=Bigg Boss Marathi: Here is what host Mahesh Manjrekar has to say about Marathi Manus - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref> This is the first and only adaption of ''Bigg Boss'' so far to have its language affiliation in the show's official name. The prize money is announced to be {{INRConvert|50|l}}. [[Megha Dhade]] emerged as the winner of First season while [[Pushkar Jog]] emerged as the first runner up of the show.\n\n=== Bigg Boss (Malayalam) ===\n{{Main|Bigg Boss (Malayalam TV series)}}\n''Bigg Boss'' is the [[Malayalam]] adaption for ''Bigg Boss'' which is produced by Star India and aired on Asianet.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/mohanlal-host-bigg-boss-malayalam-heres-all-you-need-know-769499|title=Mohanlal to host Bigg Boss Malayalam: Here's all you need to know|last=P|first=Mrudula|work=International Business Times, India Edition|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> Veteran actor Mohanlal has been roped in to host the show<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/bigg-boss-malayalam-mohanlal-show-to-begin-from-june-24-5201679/|title=Bigg Boss Malayalam: Mohanlal\u2019s show to begin from June 24|date=2018-06-02|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-US}}</ref> and the Lonavala house is being used.The voice of big boss is still a mystery<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/malayalam/bigg-boss-malayalam-exclusive-season-one-to-be-shot-in-mumbai/articleshow/64259002.cms|title=Bigg Boss Malayalam exclusive: Season One to be shot in Mumbai - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> for the first season. The prize money is announced to be \u20b91 crore(US$140,000). All the episodes of the show are available<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hotstar.com/tv/bigg-boss/17932|title=Hotstar: Bigg Boss Malayalam|last=|first=|date=|website=www.hotstar.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-20}}</ref> on the OTT platform Hotstar.Some new elements called 'Unseen', 'Spicy specials' and 'Bigg Boss Plus' was introduced by way of unseen and extra footage's uploaded on Hotstar. Bigg Boss Plus is aired on Asianet Plus and shows part of the day that weren't included in the episode. Sabumon Abdusamad was declared winner of Bigg Boss season 1 while Pearle Maaney was the first runner up.\n\nThe second season launched on 5 January 2020 with [[Mohanlal]] returning as host and the house situated at EVP Film City in [[Chennai]]. 17 contestants entered the house on Day 1 and later joined by 5 wildcard contestants. However due Corona scare, EdmolShine India had to stop all shows and season 2 had stoped at the 75th day.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Big Brother}}\n{{Indian reality television series}}\n\n[[Category:Indian reality television series]]\n[[Category:Endemol Shine Group franchises]]\n[[Category:Bigg Boss| ]]\n[[Category:Indian television series based on non-Indian television series]]\n", "name_user": "2409:4064:88b:9d1a::976:b8ac", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Bzfiaigz)", "url_